Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Work. Live. Play. Learn. Rest.

On the corner of Bourke Road and Huntley Street in Alexandria lies The Mill, a modern and refurbished offering of heritage space ready to be utilised by office/retail users. Join high profile tenants The Grounds of Alexandria, Next Hotels, Kafnu Serviced Offices, Under Armour, Seafolly and Mavi Jeans.

Location is key:
The Mill is situated 15 minutes from the Sydney CBD, 10 minutes from Sydney Airport, and 1km from Green Square and Mascot Train Stations. Easily accessible by multiple transport routes, the location is boosted by the amenity of The Grounds of Alexandria – South Sydney’s premier food and beverage destination that sees 15,000+ attendees each week.

What’s on offer?
Building 2: 275sqm – Building 2 is centrally positioned on site, L-Shaped, 275sqm tenancy that is undergoing a refurbishment. The upgraded space will contain polished concrete floors, high ceilings with exposed timber beams, improvement of lighting and façade upgrades reintroducing entry points via glass doors and additional windows. Building 2 is suitable for creative office users, retailers or showroom users.

Building 12: 814sqm –Building 12 has floor to ceiling glass with street frontage onto Bourke Road. Concrete floors, high ceilings, 814sqm of contiguous space, this tenancy is perfectly suited to a high-end showroom or retailer. With plans to further enhance the street frontage, Building 12 is the most high profile retail/showroom offering in Alexandria. Ground floor tenancy situated below Kafnu and Next Hotels.

Future plans for The Mill:
Over the course of the next few months, The Mill will undergo a facelift, inviting further patron interaction throughout the precinct. A new retail precinct will be developed, opening up the common area for pop up shops, weekend markets and entertainment. 

Another exciting addition to The Mill will be the entry of Next Story Group, who are bringing Next Hotels and Kafnu Serviced Offices to Building 12. With two levels of creative space including co-working, meeting rooms, fitness amenities and 36 rooms of 4.5* hotel accommodation, the offering personifies and encapsulates The Mill as not just a workplace, but rather a community.
